  "event_preview": "Talladega Superspeedway is a 2.66-mile (4.28 km) tri-oval in Lincoln, Alabama, opened in 1969 with 33-degree banking in the turns — the steepest of any NASCAR oval — and capable of sustaining two-wide drafting packs at sustained speeds above 185 mph. The Ag-Pro 300 is the eleventh race of the 2026 NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series season and the 35th running of the event, as well as the third of four Dash 4 Cash races on the calendar — with Taylor Gray, Sheldon Creed, Justin Allgaier and Jesse Love eligible for the $100,000 bonus after finishing as the top four O'Reilly Series regulars at Kansas.\n\nJeb Burton is the most recent two-time winner at Talladega in the series, but arrives having led a race-high laps in 2024 before being shuffled back in both attempts. Austin Hill holds the series record for superspeedway wins, having swept both Talladega races in 2025 — the first driver in series history to win at all three drafting-style tracks. Eleven drivers on the entry list have never made an O'Reilly Series start at Talladega, and five of the last eleven winners earned their first career series win at this venue.\n\nThe all-time qualifying pole record at Talladega for the series belongs to Jesse Love, who turned a 52.547-second lap (182.240 mph) to claim pole for the 2025 Ag-Pro 300 — the fastest solo lap in series history at the superspeedway. The fastest race lap on record belongs to Jeremy Clements, who turned a 49.640-second effort at 192.909 mph during the 2025 spring race.",
